  <Docs>
    <summary>Identifies color primaries using the CICP (Coding-independent Code Points) system defined in ITU-T H.273.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspacePrimariesCicp` identifies color primaries using the Coding-independent Code Points (CICP) system defined in ITU-T H.273 and ISO/IEC 23091-2. These values correspond to the `ColourPrimaries` field in video coding standards.

Use these values with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(SkiaSharp.SKColorspacePrimariesCicp,SkiaSharp.SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp)> to create a color space from CICP metadata embedded in image or video content.
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
